  Immediate Action Plan

  Day 1 (4-6 hours)

  1. Create production environment configurations
  2. Set up SSL certificates and HTTPS
  3. Configure basic database backups

  Day 2 (2-3 hours)

  1. Set up monitoring alerts
  2. Configure log management
  3. Performance tuning

  Day 3 (1-2 hours)

  1. Security hardening
  2. Final testing and deployment

  Small-Scale Deployment Options

  Option A: Single Server (Recommended for <100 users)

  - Everything on one VPS (4-8GB RAM)
  - Docker Compose setup
  - PostgreSQL and Redis on same server
  - Cost: $20-50/month

  Option B: Minimal Cloud Setup (100-500 users)

  - Separate database server
  - Application server with auto-scaling
  - Simple load balancer
  - Cost: $100-200/month

  Option C: Basic Kubernetes (500-1000 users)

  - Use existing K8s manifests
  - Managed database service
  - CDN for static assets
  - Cost: $200-400/month

  Quick Deployment Commands

  # 1. Environment setup
  cp .env.example .env.production

  # 2. SSL setup (Let's Encrypt)
  certbot --nginx -d yourdomain.com

  # 3. Database backup
  pg_dump opsight_db > backup_$(date +%Y%m%d).sql

  # 4. Deploy with Docker
  docker-compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d

  # 5. Health check
  curl https://yourdomain.com/api/health

  What You Can Deploy TODAY

  The platform can be deployed right now for small-scale use with:
  - Basic functionality working
  - User authentication
  - Real-time metrics
  - Mobile app support
  - CI/CD pipeline ready

  Missing only: Production configuration files and SSL setup.

  Bottom Line: You're about 2-3 days away from a fully production-ready small-scale deployment!